<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A measure of illumination, defined as the illumination of a one <a title="Candle" href="Candle">candle</a> object at a distance of one foot. One foot candle is equal to one <a title="Lumen" href="Lumen">lumen</a> per square foot. In the <a title="ANSI" href="http://printwiki.org/ANSI">ANSI</a>-prescribed <a title="Standard Viewing Conditions" href="Standard_Viewing_Conditions">standard viewing conditions</a> (such as a color booth used for color analysis), the illumination is 200 foot candles. (Also commonly spelled as one word, <em>footcandle</em>.) 
</p>
